parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause a short circuit, leading to a potential fire hazard.
symptoms: The electrical panel gets hot
wires start to burn
and the vehicle is not wired according to the manufacturer's specifications.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Fuses in Main Electrical Circuits
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of fuses in the main electrical circuits can cause a fire when using the air conditioner.
symptoms: The electrical panel gets hot
wires start to burn
and the vehicle is not wired according to the manufacturer's specifications.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the plumbing system can cause odors and water damage.
symptoms: The gray water tank overflows into the bathtub
and the vent pipe gets covered with water
causing odors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of a fuse can cause the emergency brake to disable, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle feels like it downshifted from one gear to first gear
and the emergency brake is disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto park brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move while parked, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or moves while parked
the brake shoes are worn out
the brake cable is burned and broken
the brake cable is improperly located and touching the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake overheating can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes overheat while descending grades
the brakes smoke or emit a burning smell
the brakes make a loud noise or grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auto-apply parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll freely, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is on an incline or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The auto-park brake applies itself while the vehicle is in motion
the emergency parking brake fails to hold the vehicle
the vehicle rolls freely after engaging the parking brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate parking brake system can cause the vehicle to roll freely, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is on an incline or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to hold the vehicle
the vehicle rolls freely after engaging the parking brake
the transmission does not have a "park" gear
the vehicle is heavy for the type of parking brake used.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust System Failure - Carbon Monoxide Infiltration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause carbon monoxide to infiltrate the vehicle, leading to poisoning, which can result in serious health problems, including respiratory issues, and even death.
symptoms: Dizziness
headaches
nausea
vomiting
confusion
disorientation
and respiratory problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust System Failure - Exhaust Hanger Strap Breakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The breakage of the exhaust hanger strap can cause damage to the tailpipe, leading to exhaust leaks, which can result in carbon monoxide infiltration into the vehicle, posing a risk to the health and safety of occupants.
symptoms: Loud noises from the exhaust system
vibrations
and visible damage to the tailpipe.
